==English==
===Etymology===
Greek ''[[άνά]]'', "up to", + ''[[λόγος]]'', "ratio".

==== Adjective ====
'''analogue''' (Spelling variant (US): '''analog''')

#Of a device, using a continuous spectrum of values as opposed to a set of discrete values; as, an analogue watch

